sentences: Halil İbrahim Ergün (born September 8, 1946) is a Turkish stage, movie and television series actor.
Ergün debuted in cinema with director Yilmaz Güney in 1974.
In 2006, he starred in the popular television series Yaprak Dökümü as Ali Rıza Bey.

Ergün was honored with "Best Actor" award in the theater and cinema, including from Golden Orange Film Festival in 1995 for "Böcek" and from Adana Golden Boll Film Festival in 1995 for "Böcek" and again in 1996 for "Mum Kokulu Kadınlar".

Ergün was honored with "Best Actor" award in the theater and cinema, including from Golden Orange Film Festival in 1995 for "Böcek" and from Adana Golden Boll Film Festival in 1995 for "Böcek" and again in 1996 for "Mum Kokulu Kadınlar".

Ergün was honored with "Best Actor" award in the theater and cinema, including from Golden Orange Film Festival in 1995 for "Böcek" and from Adana Golden Boll Film Festival in 1995 for "Böcek" and again in 1996 for "Mum Kokulu Kadınlar".
He received an honorary lifelong achievement award in 2007 from Golden Orange Film Festival.

1995 "Best Actor" International Adana Golden Boll Film Festival
1996 "Best Actor" International Adana Golden Boll Film Festival
2007 "Life Achievement" International Antalya Golden Orange Film Festival
